  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>
      <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\frac {}           {\Gamma  \vdash  ()\Leftarrow \text {unit}}(\mathtt {Unit-I\Leftarrow })]]></fr:tex>
    </fr:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
  <fr:backmatter>
    <fr:tree toc="false" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
      <fr:frontmatter>
        <fr:title text="Context">Context</fr:title>
        <fr:authors />
      </fr:frontmatter>
      <fr:mainmatter>
        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" expanded="false" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:anchor>532</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">type-systems-0004</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>type-systems-0004.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Bidirectional simply-typed lambda calculus with () : {unit} and type equality">Bidirectional simply-typed lambda calculus with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[() : \text {unit}]]></fr:tex> and type equality</fr:title>
            <fr:authors />
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>A bidirectional variant of the <fr:link type="local" href="type-systems-0003.xml" addr="type-systems-0003" title="Simply-typed lambda calculus with () : {unit} and type equality">simply-typed lambda calculus</fr:link>
(BDSTLC) can be expressed as follows:</fr:p>
            <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:anchor>272</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">type-systems-0006</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>type-systems-0006.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Variable synthesis">Variable synthesis</fr:title>
                <fr:authors />
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>
                  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\frac {\begin {array}{cc}              (x:A) \in  \Gamma              \end {array}}             {\Gamma  \vdash  x \Rightarrow  A}(\mathtt {Var\Rightarrow })]]></fr:tex>
                </fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
              <fr:backmatter />
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:anchor>273</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">type-systems-0007</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>type-systems-0007.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Annotation synthesis">Annotation synthesis</fr:title>
                <fr:authors />
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>
                  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\frac {\begin {array}{cc}              \Gamma  \vdash  e \Leftarrow  A            \end {array}}            {\Gamma  \vdash  (e::A) \Rightarrow  A}(\mathtt {Anno\Rightarrow })]]></fr:tex>
                </fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
              <fr:backmatter />
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:anchor>274</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">type-systems-0008</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>type-systems-0008.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Arrow introduction checking">Arrow introduction checking</fr:title>
                <fr:authors />
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>
                  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\frac {\begin {array}{cc}              \Gamma , x:A_1 \vdash  e \Leftarrow  A_2            \end {array}}            {\Gamma  \vdash  (\lambda  x.e) \Leftarrow  A_1 \rightarrow  A_2}(\mathtt {\rightarrow  I\Leftarrow })]]></fr:tex>
                </fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
              <fr:backmatter />
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:anchor>275</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">type-systems-0009</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>type-systems-0009.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Arrow elimination synthesis">Arrow elimination synthesis</fr:title>
                <fr:authors />
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>
                  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\frac {\begin {array}{cc}              \Gamma  \vdash  e_1 \Rightarrow  A_1 \rightarrow  A_2 & \Gamma  \vdash  e_2 \Leftarrow  A_1            \end {array}}            {\Gamma  \vdash  (e_1 e_2) \Rightarrow  A_2}(\mathtt {\rightarrow  E\Rightarrow })]]></fr:tex>
                </fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
              <fr:backmatter />
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:anchor>276</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">type-systems-000A</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>type-systems-000A.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Unit introduction checking">Unit introduction checking</fr:title>
                <fr:authors />
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>
                  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\frac {}           {\Gamma  \vdash  ()\Leftarrow \text {unit}}(\mathtt {Unit-I\Leftarrow })]]></fr:tex>
                </fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
              <fr:backmatter />
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:anchor>277</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">type-systems-000B</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>type-systems-000B.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Subsumption checking">Subsumption checking</fr:title>
                <fr:authors />
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>
                  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\frac {\begin {array}{cc}              \Gamma  \vdash  e \Rightarrow  A & A = B            \end {array}}            {\Gamma  \vdash  e \Leftarrow  B}(\mathtt {Sub\Leftarrow })]]></fr:tex>
                </fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
              <fr:backmatter />
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:p>Explanation of the rules:
  <fr:ol><fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathtt {Var\Rightarrow }]]></fr:tex> has no typing premise, but since <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x:A]]></fr:tex> is in the
    context, we can synthesize the type of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex>. Checking would require knowing the type
    of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> in advance (i.e., from the term).</fr:li>

    <fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathtt {Anno\Rightarrow }]]></fr:tex> synthesizes the type of an annotated term. Here,
    synthesis and checking flip from synthesis to checking. Important to note that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e ::     A]]></fr:tex> here is not a typing judgement—which belong to the metalanguage and do not have
    type—but a term annotated with a type and therefore part of the object language.</fr:li>

    <fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathtt {\rightarrow  I\Leftarrow }]]></fr:tex> checks a lambda abstraction against a function
    (arrow) type. Synthesizing the type of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\lambda  x.e]]></fr:tex> would require synthesizing the
    type of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e]]></fr:tex>, but not all bodies synthesize, e.g., <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[()]]></fr:tex>. Furthermore, even when the
    body does synthesize, the type of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> must be known in advance; the body may depend
    on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex>. However, synthesis doesn't know the type of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex>, because it cannot accept
    type arguments, and because its type is not yet known, it is not yet in the context.
    It would need to guess the type, which is something we are trying to avoid.</fr:li>

    <fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathtt {\rightarrow  E\Rightarrow }]]></fr:tex>, or <fr:em>arrow elimination</fr:em>, synthesizes the 
    type of an application. Synthesize of the function type in the first premise is
    possible, because

      <fr:ol><fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathtt {Var\Rightarrow }]]></fr:tex> can synthesize the type of a variable</fr:li>
        <fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathtt {Anno\Rightarrow }]]></fr:tex> can synthesize the type of an annotated term</fr:li>
        <fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathtt {\rightarrow  E\Rightarrow }]]></fr:tex> can synthesize the type of an application</fr:li></fr:ol>

      Once the function type is synthesized, we can check the argument against the
      parameter type which can be obtained by analyzing the synthesized function type.</fr:li>
   
    <fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathtt {Unit-I\Leftarrow }]]></fr:tex> checks the unit term against the unit type.</fr:li>

    <fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathtt {Sub\Leftarrow }]]></fr:tex> checks a term against its expected type by synthesizing
    the term's type and then checking that it is equal to the expected type. Note that the
    mode flips here like it does in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathtt {Anno\Rightarrow }]]></fr:tex>, but in the opposite
    direction, from checking to synthesis.</fr:li></fr:ol></fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
      <fr:backmatter />
    </fr:tree>
  </fr:backmatter>
</fr:tree>
